Developer updates & resources

Yesterday, we announced a bunch of new API products and features at DevDay San Francisco. You can catch up on all the action at openai.com/devday ( http://openai.com/devday ) , and we’ll be adding recordings of the keynote, breakout sessions, and developer community talks in a few weeks.

DevDay ( https://openai.com/devday/ )

-----------------
*Product Updates*
-----------------

*Realtime API*

With the new Realtime API ( https://openai.com/index/introducing-the-realtime-api/ ) , you can now create low-latency speech-to-speech experiences—think ChatGPT's Advanced Voice, but for your own app, using the six preset voices already supported in the API. Until now, building voice into apps required stitching together multiple models, causing latency or unnatural interactions. Realtime API is rolling out in beta to all developers. Check out our docs ( https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/realtime ) or use the sample library ( https://github.com/openai/openai-realtime-api-beta ) to get started.

*Prompt Caching*

Now available to all developers, Prompt Caching ( https://openai.com/index/api-prompt-caching/ ) saves you 50% on cached inputs over uncached inputs and reduces latency by reusing recently seen input tokens. It’s automatically applied on the latest versions of GPT-4o, GPT-4o mini, o1-preview and o1-mini, as well as fine-tuned versions of those models. Read more in our docs ( https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/prompt-caching/prompt-caching ).

*Model Distillation*

Many of you are already performing distillation on your own, but it involves multiple, complex steps. We’re introducing a new Model Distillation ( https://openai.com/index/api-model-distillation/ ) workflow to train smaller, cost-efficient models on the intelligence of larger, more capable models for specific tasks—all on the OpenAI platform. This includes new features like Stored Completions ( http://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/chat/create#chat-create-store ) , which helps you generate datasets for distillation, and Evals ( http://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/evals ) (beta), which helps you create and run custom evaluations on our platform. Get started with our docs ( https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/distillation ).

*Vision Fine-Tuning*

You can now fine-tune GPT-4o with both text and images ( https://openai.com/index/introducing-vision-to-the-fine-tuning-api/ ). This enables applications like advanced visual search, improved object detection for autonomous vehicles, and more accurate image analysis. Learn more in docs ( https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/fine-tuning/vision ).

*Free Fine-tuning training tokens (applies to Model Distillation and Vision Fine-Tuning!)*

Now through October 31, we’re offering 1M free training tokens per day on GPT-4o and 2M free training tokens per day on GPT-4o mini. After that, pricing snaps back to our standard fine-tuning prices, which you can find on our API pricing page ( https://openai.com/api/pricing/ ).

*GPT-4o update*

Starting today, we're updating the default GPT-4o model to gpt-4o-2024-08-06 , offering 50% lower input token costs and 33% lower output token costs! Point your code at the gpt-4o or gpt-4o-2024-08-06 model to get the savings.

*OpenAI o1 availability*

We’re expanding API access to our new reasoning models, OpenAI o1-preview and o1-mini, to usage tier 3 ( https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/rate-limits/usage-tiers ). We've also increased rate limits ( https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/rate-limits/usage-tiers?context=tier-three ) for developers on tiers 4 and 5 to 10,000 RPM, matching those of GPT-4o. We're working hard to bring access to more usage tiers soon.

*Generate in the Playground*

Easily generate prompts, function definitions, and structured output schemas in the playground using the Generate button. The generated prompts provide a solid starting point for your projects before you build out more specific requirements. Get started in the Playground ( https://platform.openai.com/playground/chat?models=gpt-4o ).

